Bring a large pot of water to a boil, season with salt. Cook pasta 1 minute under required cooking time, drain and toss with 2 tbsp olive oil. Place on sheet tray to cool down. In a blender combine garlic, 1/2 pine nuts, and basil, pulse for a few seconds. Slowly drizzle in remaining olive oil to emulsify the pesto. Add half the Parmigiano and pulse, season with salt and pepper, set aside. In a large bowl combine, pesto and pasta and stir to incorporate. Fold in remaining cheeses, cherry tomatoes and pine nuts.